{"text": "A basic test simulation with incredibly random questions. I found it quite funny that I was told \"Obviously, you know this topic quite well.\" upon completion of a test labelled 'Truth or Fiction' with a score of only 57% correct. Which itself contained a myriad of completely bizarre random questions containing no correlation to any specific subject. I decided to play through another test labelled 'Animals' to which I was given questions ranging from relatively easy common knowledge to things only a zoologist would know the answer to. I can't say I enjoyed my short play through very much but for what it's worth, it does what it says on the box as some might say and it does have some saving grace with being able to craft your own test for friends to play through. Overall, it's not something I'd personally play when trying to unwind after work but I suppose it's what it says it is, a Brain Test and being able to create and share your own tests is pretty cool so I'll give it a thumbs up. If I could make a suggestion though, it would be to add achievements and personally, I'd advise lowering the price from Â£2.89 to something more reasonable like Â£0.79.", "appid": "1350390", "steamid": "profiles/76561197982273259", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601467200.0}
