{"text": "An early review since I only have around 10 hours in this game so far. Firstly, I want to confirm a few facts when people say that this game seems impossible to play or is extremely difficult to the point of quitting very early.  >> This game requires a lot of patience and understanding before you can actually start one-shotting enemies. It's not like your average RPG wherein you just rush into enemies and beat them to death or just take them out via indirect attacks.  >> The game is very close to the Souls Series since the mechanics are quite similar but instead of rolling and dodging, you have to deflect or counter all enemy attacks and then take them out. >> Be aware that the game is VERY MUCH based on Stealth Tactics. There are several methods which can make your journey throughout the game very easy and satisfying if you can come up with strategies or even rely on a few walkthroughs if you feel like you are stuck at some point.  >> There are definitely several unique stages including boss fights which are quite difficult and test your limits and skills but then again, if you have the patience, understanding and practice, your journey would be extremely enjoyable.  >> Like the Souls Series, I have also been playing Sekiro using a Mouse and Keyboard and not a controller (Just my personal choice and I was never a big fan of controllers to begin with), and so far it's been very satisfying for me. I am not sure how the difficulty or the handling of mechanics and controls would alter the gameplay for me but for some people it does matter so it's upto you to go ahead and check it out. So far, I have been really enjoying this game. It's definitely challenging but extremely fun and satisfying at the same time. You get a variety of techniques which you can unlock and play around with, a fair share of fun yet difficult moments and combined with the amazing graphics and lore; this game has been very very well-worth for me so far! Rated :- 9/10", "appid": "814380", "steamid": "profiles/76561197999448753", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562068800.0}
