{"text": "Finally joined the bandwagon concerning this game, and I'm glad I'm aboard. It's one of the most immersive experiences I've had in a while, and I'm sure one which will have lasting effects. This is the kind of game which will plant seeds. It becomes embedded in your psyche, Not coincidentally, the psyche is at the forefront of every interaction you will undergo while playing. Disco Elysium requires a smart player. And not just because of the mountains of text you're required to read, but because of the many concepts and references (many only in this fictional universe) interspersed throughout. Plus, many of the moral choices and considerations require great thought.  And it's all rewarding. First of all, the writing is superb, and deserving of a pulitzer. I don't say this lightly. It's better written than most books. The myriads of diverse dialogue choices all are done with conviction, and you really feel like your choices have consequence. And most of the time, they do. Failing skill checks often brings about unforeseen rewards, and seemingly inconsequential pieces of dialogue come back later. It's really not so much an RPG as it is an adventure game, however. It has RPG elements, similar to Quest For Glory and the skill advancements.  It's astonishingly deep and emotionally intelligent. If you don't get the feels from this game, you are soulless. There is much humor, laden through this waltz of despair. You and your character will have many sinking feelings and dawning realizations up until the final curtain. All the characters are unique and likeable/loatheable/multifaceted. You really begin to care about your character (and Kim) and the world around you,  The influence from Planescape Torment is palpable, and that's A-ok by me. They even thank Chris Avellone at the end.  It also reminded me of QFG (as previously mentioned), Divinity Original Sin 2, True Detective (especially with their misanthropic Bukowski-like banter), Shutter Island, and the miniseries Mosaic.", "appid": "632470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198273762327", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594555200.0}
