{"text": "After so many years waiting for the sequel to the first RoR game, the   comes with an   masterpiece. Though it is in Early Access and lack things like the   that enable you to freely change the style of gameplay, RoR2, now in a beautifully designed 3D, is already one of the best games that I've played. The always changing outcome of a single run based on player choices and luck, the rising difficulty based on time played and the secrets/challenges to uncover, fulfill me with will to play again and again. The changes on connection,  , made it very easy to play with friends. The new  , although a big laggy sometimes based on the \"host\" connection, works absolutely fine and adds extra fun to the trip. The price may be a bit high for now, but that's understandable for a game in EA that needs players who are willing to share opinions and help the game growing process.  After playing many hours, discussing and discovering the secrets and new content that doesn't was in the first game, my conclusion is that Risk of Rain 2, after a great week on its debut, has conquered almost everyone that played it. With 6 playable characters at the moment, it can fit a very large variety of playstyles. And the devs shall be making it even greater with new content and bug-fixing updates.", "appid": "632360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198098440825", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1554292800.0}
