{"text": "As the typical belief that a +18 game will only be linear and without much history is true in most such games, but in \"acting lessons\" broke the typical paradigm of the +18 game, it is a game that made a home run into space, has an immersive story, \"porn\" is part of the relationship and interaction between the characters, it has twists, dramas, scenes that worry\"s you about the good being of some of the people. Not only this, besides laughing out loud, you cry in several scenes, the plot has a few twists (not spoiler), despite just showing almost images and scenes it is a game that I can recommend to anyone who can buy it, plus if you analyze it well, it gives several lessons about life itself, it is a beautiful game, my CONGRATULATIONS TO THE CREATOR, (although It kills me with the half bitter end ) I hope that DR. PINCKCAKE continue creating such beautiful games. 9.0/10", "appid": "1045520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090321265", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571745600.0}
{"text": "This game is an awesome and is addictive with Starbound and Terraria elements to it, but with its own type of flavor. The game is early access has occasional hiccups, but can be easily fixed with an update or two. Itâ€™s a refreshing take on 2D sandbox/rpg type of games which is a good commodity.  Letâ€™s start with the gameplay. It starts out rather easy as you can get a short tutorial on what to do. You can easily manage controls on an Xbox controller or PlayStation controller which can be helpful. The graphics are pixelated like any other retro game. Iâ€™m a fan of these retro games as I grew up in the 80's and 90's playing those console games in their prime. The skilling up/leveling up system is very unique and different from Starbound and Terraria which makes this game stand on its own. I enjoyed exploring and creating my homes, teleport points, forges, and loved the crafting aspect inside of it. This game is very time consuming and can be very addictive at the same time.  The game isnâ€™t perfect and still is an early access game which comes with its bugs and glitches. The game has unusually long load times when you first start out which I found awkward knowing this is a pixel 2d sandbox game and isnâ€™t a really big game that should be doing so. I found that it did take much more memory than expected as well which I heard the developer is seeking to fix. In terms of the multiplayer aspect, there should be some dedicated servers steam side to help everyone connect with each other to make this game even more fun. I hope that this is also fixed and implemented in the finalized version so I can even give this a higher grade on my review. Anyways I found this game to be quite fun, addictive, time consuming, and refreshingly new. I hope this game can fix these glitches and whatnot to make this an even better game.   7.5/10", "appid": "280520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044920564", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1465732800.0}
