{"text": "I've never heard of this game before and yet it still amazes me how perfectly well this gem of a platformer is crafted. I'd go as far as saying it's even better than Super Mario World on the SNES in terms of variation brought here through presenting a new game changing mechanic in each and every level of the game. Like in newer Mario titles all levels are accessible from an overworld map, but here you can collect coins on the map itself too if you got stuck in the game. You can even change the layout of the map as you like to by removing obstacles or placing bridges for easier navigation around the overworld or to reach places you couldn't get to otherwise. Replay value is extremely high, as the game collects stats about everything you achieve and by doing so permanently insists on you to get better and better until you reach the real final ending. Furthermore when completed you get time challenge modes for every individual level as well to further improve your gameplay. And of course there are lots of secrets everywhere. Should you get this game? As a platform addict absolutely yes, as a longterm Mario lover you might even find ideas Nintendo hasn't added to their well known plumber yet ... This game is a steal, even at normal pricing.", "appid": "656970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052707118", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588766400.0}
{"text": "I love playing this game on my leisure time. I play under the German faction and my specialty is - Recon SDKfz 222 driving/ and gunning. I thoroughly enjoy making lots of enemies come after me using their rockets, planes, or anti-armored grenades. It really helps draw out the focus of players from the objectives. The best part of it is when noobs think they can drive out/run out in the open towards me thinking they are sneaking/rushing only to end up dead. Even noobish pilots think they can nose dive shoot at me when in reality, the shells will take out their plane and all I'll need to do is repair the damages done.  But now...like all other H&G players...there is time for ranting.  From the German faction perspective, my biggest complaint has to be that german fighter planes get less bombs than the other factions. I understand the devs like to relive the WW2 experience and make Germany lose the war by nerfing weaponry and bolstering other factions but let's get real. They need to learn humiliation. Just cause one faction's players start being good at killing doesn't mean it's time for a nerf. All in all, I actually do NOT have complaints about Germany aside from the planes. I just am tired of seeing the other two factions receiving bonuses, and weaponry simply to \"even out\" the fighting. All in all the game is free. The game is playable. The game is an FPS WW2 era game. The maps are huge so you won't feel contained. Vehicles exist. People running out and others camping. It's fun! Microtransactions exist BUT so do warbonds. You can live off and ride off warbonds rather than just paying over and over and over. If you know how to save you can make more gold just from warbonds. Of course, you can always grind! Lastly, my favorite part is the community. I've made lots of friends and remember them by name. I can join matches and talk about a player and at least 2 people would know who I'm talking about. I just love that. Anyways thanks for reading!. - Blackpaw Santana", "appid": "227940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198148702632", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1505217600.0}
