{"text": "Experience a game unlike anything else. This unique masterpiece is a perfect fit for people enjoying sarcastical and controversial views on (American) society. The story is about daily errands tasked by your \"lovely\" wife and the gameplay only gets as violent as you let to provoke yourself. You can finish the game with zero kills or nuke the whole town to Hell while pissing (!) on people until they puke. xD It's really not a game for fun killers taking it seriously and that's why it gets every rating from 0% to 100%. Even the developers are mucking about themselves by putting their studio ingame and using the restroom as an office. :D The \"missions\" have a great variety, from trivial stuff like getting milk from the supermarket or bringing back a book to the library up to pissing on your Dad's grave and running around with a Gimp Suit downtown. Other activities include visiting a Taliban terror camp or Uncle Dave's drug farm. Apart from the story you can also just run around and enjoy exploring the town like a free-roam sandbox game. The game was orginal released back in 2003 but thanks to Greenlight got a second spring on Steam, a new add-on called \"Lost Paradise\" and still (!!) receives regular updates from the developers - after more than 15 years. It's a true Labour of Love; it's proudly banned in Australia, New Zealand and Malaysia; it's funny and totally insane; it uses cats as silencer and counts the number of kicked in doors; it has 69 achievements (the number is NOT a coincidence, you get it, right?) and even featured in Black Eyed Peas \"Where's the Love?\" music video. As you can see the impact of this game is as unique as itself and worth a try!", "appid": "223470", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968240913", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "27", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511438400.0}
