{"text": "- 24 hours I don't know how to start. This game and 'Just Cause 3' were my very first steam purchases. This reminds me some nostalgic memoriesðŸ˜. I don't know why I underestimated this game. Whatever, THIEF (2014) is the reboot of the classic 'Thief' series. The game is set in 'The City', a dark fantasy world inspired by Victorian, Gothic, and steampunk aesthetics. You control Garrett, a master thief who has exceptional thieving skills...Ok let's get to the PROS and CONS>>  -   -  I cannot remember another. If I find, I will add here.  -  Story - 7/10 Gameplay - 8/10 Level Design - 9-10 Overall - 8/10 Most of my friends have this their library..But if you don't have, buy this during a sale... Thanks for reading....Some information is collected from wikipedia", "appid": "239160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198394232524", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "27", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1558353600.0}
{"text": "After finished the mission solo, I must say, It's one of those cool missions on the series, There were several shortcut paths that I said to myself \"man, wish I had a chem kit\" while I chose to carried a wire cutter. Some of the shortcuts are really resourceful in this one. The map design is also remarkable, the lighting is great in many dark and dim areas. The fact that the area of the mission takes place in the nearby area of Hell or High Water giving you the nostalgic feeling and also making the world more believable.  I finished it with heat level full in the first time and It felt like I john wicked the way through the mission (you know... a church and all)  All in all a total fun episode to start a second season. It's not too hard to do it alone, and it's not too easy or short to make you feel lacking. I'll have to replay it again and again, cause it's that good!", "appid": "987170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198063418879", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543492800.0}
