{"text": "I can recommend OutDrive for what it is. An interactive 80s style music demo, featuring a very very easy never-ending driving theme. If you are looking for an actual driving game, this is not it. The music and visuals are awesome for as long as the soundtrack lasts. A good hour and a half. By that time you will have seen the 3 possible routs several times, and you probably want to stop playing. The driving is too easy to be challenging at any point, except fot the very first time, due to \"unexpected\" controller settings.. (which you need to setup every time you play). I don't think I'll play the game again, but for me, the 2 hours I spent driving in this \"Blood Dragon\" laser world with 80s electro-synth-pop in 2017 production quality, was well worth the 50c I paid on sale.", "appid": "441870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135792443", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "30", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1509364800.0}
