{"text": "â˜‘Incredible Graphics which still hold up massively for a game released in 2015 â˜‘Story is tough gripping with lots of deeply interesting characters & lore â˜‘Combat is extremely satisfying, with countless different builds you can go so you won't get bored, ever. â˜‘Very addictive always feel like coming back and trying a new build/dialogue options â˜‘Music is near Skyrim levels of breathtaking with a heavy influence of it, so if you liked Skyrims ambient music & fast battle music you'll love this too â˜‘Side quests are nearly always fun to do with lots of interesting concepts, returning characters from previous games and crazy enemies â˜‘Can import your save from The Witcher 2: Assassin Of Kings which effects some in-game story decisions â˜‘Most of the characters in this game are very likeable/hateble in a very, very good way â˜‘Tsundere goth girl that is in love with you but doms you around â˜’EXTREMELY BUGGY. One of actually no, this is the most buggy game I've played in recent years. A list of some of the few hundred bugs I encountered were: Crashing, loading screens not ending, enemies being stuck in a T pose and easy to kill, falling through the map, not being able to use signs unless you reload, potions not going off and the worst one I came across by far is Level Scailing. TURN THIS OFF! As even RATS can one shot you if you reach a certain level which is absolutely ridiculous and certain fights like the Djinn one becomes impossible with it on if you are a higher level then the quest â˜’Noticed in dialogue, if you choose an option rarely Geralt doesn't exactly say what you picked just either along the lines of it barely or not relating to it at all. Very rare this happens but noticed it a couple times playing it through twice â˜’Crafting is VERY expensive late game, so expensive you have to keep finding ways to farm money if you don't have contracts left and want to keep crafting gear/weapons by killing high level enemies and selling their weapons which doesn't always work as smiths have a set amount of money which can run out if you sell them too much Overall this is a phenomenal game I would arguably say is better then Zelda: BOTW, but bugs hold it back by a lot. In BOTW there is a lot of great ones like launching across the map riding your shield or beating the game from the get go but in this game, the bugs are ONLY an annoyance always hindering your gameplay. 8/10", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118979081", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582718400.0}
