{"text": "\"Because nobody likes playing with cheaters.\" Im a former Quake / 1.6 pro-player and thinking that I cheat is just an excuse to your brain, because you can't believe that my skill is just better than you. Hahaha you guys make me laugh :) This community is full of egos, hard headedâ™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥HEADS, and people who think they are legends to CSGO, and really, shouldn't even be playing the game. I love this community, the forums never ceases to amaze me, fill me with RAGE and LOVE and HATE and SADNESS all in a couple threads. The one thing that pisses me off the MOST about the CSGO COMMUNITY is this. One person can be targetted and attacked and destroyed simply because they have made people mad IN A VIDEO GAME. Let me step back and tell you, this is a video game. You are all PLAYING A VIDEO GAME. The fact that you get so BUTT HURT over someone calling you WORSE than THEY are, means you must have been picked on SOMETHING FIERCE in highschool and university? My Message Nobody is exempt from being made fun of and this is exactly the way it should be. As long as I have a shred of free speech left I will relentlessly make fun of everybody and everything. From Valve's â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ Anti-Cheat, rednecks to chimps to Jews to cucked Swedes to Marxists, feminists and hordes of \"refugees\" enriching Europe including the delusional leftists supporting it. No political correctness will stop me and certainly not the kind of people who value \"The amazing VAC\" with no message whatsoever over free speech and political satire about serious events. They're apathetic cowards and not part of the follower base this steam profile is intended for. Feel free to remove me if my message are too serious for you, there's plenty of room in the vast sand of distraction on Steam for you to bury your head in. Your safe space will not last forever. My message has always been political and always had some kind of underlying message, while still retaining the kind of comedic value that will never be attractive to the masses. Yes, the topics changed dramatically, but so has the world. My way of telling it did not. Seeing how my fan base grew by 700 over the past month and the people who have been here since '14 are still commenting, people seem to like it. Feel free to correct me if I'm wrong.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198323102405", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "19", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1539864000.0}
