{"text": "After almost 100 hours playtime, I have finished Assassins Creed III with 100% It is a great game and brings the story about Desmond finally to an end. Connor is not the charming person as we know Ezio from Assassins Creed 2, but during the story we learn much about his motives and goals and we can see a development in his character. Above the story missions there are so many sidequests to do, which you can spend so much time. Naval missions, hunting quests, upgrading your ship, missions for thieves and other guilds and building up your own little settlement. The basics, free running and combat, have been simplified and improved.  In my opinion I only can say that if you liked Assassins Creed 1 +2, you will have fun with part 3.", "appid": "208480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061172240", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1540814400.0}
