{"text": "This is really fun! It's like a mix between puzzle and tactics, since it's not only about just destroying the enemies, but also board control in different ways (positioning, moving the opponent's pieces etc.) It's a really fresh and creative approach on TBS. It's very smooth, relatively fast-paced, minimalistic, yet surprisingly deep. It's not as unforgiving or even unfair as FTL sometimes, but can still be very challenging (I wouldn't compare these two anyway). And there are lots of customization options to your squad, adding replayability.  And one thing I really have to note: The UI is outstanding! Everything is neatly arranged, plain and comprehensible. A lot of AAA productions can take a leaf from this book! To me this is a nice game for in between, when you don't want to play any more time consuming games. Maybe it's not worth the 15 bux to everyone, but should it be on sale in the future and you like TBS, this is a must buy IMO. P.S.: I haven't encountered a single bug so far. Seems very polished to me.", "appid": "590380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006507699", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520769600.0}
