{"text": "DISCLAIMER: English is not my first language, so sorry for any grammatical errors. I played all of the Dead Island games that Techland made. I completed Original Dead Island 2 times, I finished Ryder White's DLC, I finished Riptide and I even played Dead Island Epidemic. But this game, is the best thing Techland ever made. It is fun, it is addictive, it is awesome. I tried to play this game all kind of ways, I played it alone, I played it with my new friend, and I tried to play it with Zombie invasions on. And even if it is super fun to play with your friend, or just some random person that connected to your game, and even if zombie invasions are really cool to, I will highly recommend you to play it offline, without players able to connect to you and without zombie invasions. It is the best way to play this game in order to feel it, how developers wanted you to feel it. If dead island franchise was build for 4 players to play together, and it is pretty boring to play alone, Dying Light was meant to be the game you suppose to play alone. Because there are a lot of moments when the game maybe not scary, but creppy and nervous for sure, and when you play with someone, game stops to be scary and nervouse. And play it on a Hard difficulty, because thats the best difficulty to play at, because this game is meant to be hardcore.", "appid": "239140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198188762847", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1507809600.0}
