{"text": "Sundered, a Metroid-roguelite. The interesting thing is the map system. while every death regenerates the world, the short-cuts you find/unlock stay, and stay in the same place.  This sort of structural thing is very interesting.  The teleports in rogue legacy are easier, but sundered splits it into 3 world/levels to basically do the same thing, with added complexity. Though \"rush to boss room\" only got noticable with 1-3 of them. Few others remembering where to go to fight them was a thing. Amazing art and animation!!!  Probably some of the best platforming controls I've ever used. Combat is mostly boring mash 1 button affair. (it has a few moves, but they are mostly inefficient / extra effort for little gain.) Combat is still compelling though, and the boss fights really shine through. Also of note: Death has 0 effect on xp/money though. only resets you to spawn room and remakes the world.", "appid": "535480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009392461", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1523534400.0}
