{"text": "Review based on Early Access 11/6/15 First of all i like the concept of the game which is indeed a bit like Harvast Moon. DidnÂ´t play long enough yet to go through all content but there seems a lot to do. Off course you have your farm but also a town with quite a few locations, horse racing-betting and for so far IÂ´ve seen a nice story and lotÂ´s of npc. Graphics are simple but very nice.  On the other hand this is an early access build and there are still some things that need polishing. Most anoying is that it looks like keys are not always responding. Maybe itÂ´s just me not standing exactly in the right position, but if itÂ´s mentioned in some other reviews i hope the devs will look after it. Other point is that you have to click a lot during conversations with npc's to get to the next page. It hapen't me quite a few times i clicked to fast and skipped the screen were i had to choose a response without knowing which option i had chosen. Maybe the devs kan think of something smart to prevent this. Also i hope steam achivements will be added in the future. Nice promising game for everyone who loves farming games. At this moment I think asking price is (even with EA discount) to high for it's current state. But it's well worth to put on your wishlist and pick it up when development is a little further.", "appid": "328220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070118218", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1446811200.0}
