{"text": "Blood Money is simply the best Game of the whole Hitman Series, this is what should have set the path for all following releases, \"Hitman: Absolution\" wasn't a bad game but it certainly did not come close to the real Hitman experience since it was more of a action game and the two other ones that followed are packed with DLC's etc. that easily cost you 70-200 and they still lack the experience of this game. I wish they would have released a follow up to Blood Money with the exact same gameplay and new contracts. If you want the full Hitman experience, I recommend to get Blood Money. Each contract can be done the way you want to (of course the more of a ghost you are the better) and there are a ton of ways to complete a contract in a clean way. The contracts and the environments give a realistic vibe. Once you get into it you'll notice how your stealth skills improve try after try. The soundtrack delivers an incredible atmosphere. There are many details that the other Hitman games lack. This is also one of the best stealth games ever made. I spent a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ load of hours playing this game before it was on steam back in the days, probably my most played game and I still come back to this one on here since no other Hitman gives me these kind of vibes.", "appid": "6860", "steamid": "profiles/76561197977159343", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584360000.0}
