{"text": "I don't quite understand why this game gets so much hate; sure it's not a \"game\" in the traditional sense and there's not much actual \"gameplay\" involved, but have people forgotten the FMV games back in 90s? If anything, FMV adventures come as close as it gets to classic old-school games because the earliest adventure games actually used to be like this. So basically, the entire game consists of full-motion videos (a.k.a. movies) with real actors in them and you're given a few choices on how to advance the plot. Let me start by pointing out that most of the wrong choices are pure comedy gold. Sure, it's cringy and weird but it's one of those cases that \"it's so bad it's almost good\". I just couldn't stop laughing after watching some of the scenes play out after making the blatant wrong choice. There's also a commentary on every choice after the scene is over which actually does a pretty decent job of explaining what you did right or wrong. Sure, you can't just learn how to score dates in real life from playing a scripted video game but that's not the point. At least, that wasn't the point for me. If you go into this expecting to become a dating guru, you'd probably be disappointed but if you treat it as a comedy, you could have a great time laughing at the situations and dialog. Another criticism that I often see is that this game provides false information about dating, that is not true at all. I mean, there aren't any super secret mystical magic words that will instantly get you any girl in this game or any other game (because no such thing exists in the real world) but it does give you some basic understanding of how things work. For example, it does tell you that you should always treat women with respect even if they're rude to you. Again, expect comedy not a tutorial... - Cute girls - Some useful dating advice - Decent production quality - Hilarious dialog, very funny - Good environment and scene variety - The only gameplay element is dialog choices - Cringy presentation - Somewhat weak acting - Rather poor soundtrack - The scenes occasionally cut off abruptly - There's a small delay before you can skip a scene  6.75/10 - Decent Super Seducer is a genuinely hilarious work of comedy which does provide some very basic and trivial dating advice. It's a FMV adventure with the only gameplay element being dialog choices. Acting has room for improvement but some of the dialog is extremely funny. Overall, I'd recommend trying it out but expect a comedy movie (not an actual dating sim).", "appid": "695920", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963259080", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549972800.0}
{"text": "Well after 145+ hours I guess it's time to write a review. I picked up this game on impulse for $7.99, thought it would be fun to mess around with a friend of mine in co-op. Somehow that turned into several months of addiction. The game has decent graphics for being an indi devoloped game (it runs on unreal engine 4), music is fitting and doesn't get annoying. One thing to note is the performance can be a bit jumpy, especially in online co-op, I can see 155 fps one second and 45 the next, but overall doesn't hurt playability in my opinion. The maps are procedurally generated each time you play and are random.  The enemy spawns are dictated by your item pick ups which makes for some intense sitiuations. If you're low on ammo, do you grab that box of pistol ammo and risk some high level spawns or try to melee to save ammo? After each game you are awarded currency called \"karma\". You spend karm leveling up your gear, called \"trinkets\". The addiction comes from once you start being able to hunt for demon chests which have the random high level trinkets in them that make your character very powerful. It's a bit like Diablo in that regard.  The game also has a small dedicated community that are awesome to play with and willing to help new players get into the game. After  a while single player gets boring but co-op is where the fun is! Just be prepared to die a lot, the game is pretty unforgiving on the higher dfifficulties. The games creator, Blue actively reads the forums and continues to take suggestions on ways to improve the game with future updates. Overall, I highly recomend Unloved if you like fast paced FPS's. Special shout out to Zod, sobored3440, Moki, Linkowiezi, JIm, Godsdoomer, and tendersurrender. Playing with those guys is a blast, don't hesistate to jump into one of their games if you see them!", "appid": "321270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198175178995", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487246400.0}
