{"text": "Stupidly late to the party, but here we go Bought this game back when it released, got a good 55% through it, then just never picked it up again... until a few days ago, and I managed to finish it. â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, what a game. By far the absolute best VR experience I've ever had (and possibly ever will get). It's incredible quite how immersed you manage to get in this - it's  Story-wise, come on, let's not kid ourselves here, it's a fully fledged Half-Life game. The story isn't emotional at all, but it's incredibly riveting. Only a few amount of important characters, with no specific antagonist except for just \"The Combine\" TM, but the intricacy of the HL-universe is enough to get you hooked in. I'd never played another HL game before this, but that really doesn't matter. Gameplay is incredible. Puzzles are original and interesting; not so difficult that you have to be smart to solve them, but they're not total 'gimme's either. Most of them play off the same few mechanical tricks, but in interesting ways that require you to genuinely stop and think about what you're trying to accomplish. In terms of combat, they really hit the nail on the head here. Controls feel natural, even in the heat of battle, and the guns play super well into this. Perfect execution on the items like grenades or medkits. 10/10, best VR game ever", "appid": "546560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100112667", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602417600.0}
