{"text": "For the game that was published in 2014, the graphics are pretty high rated. I love the fact that this game is very dark and morbid. As an Assassins Creed fan, anything remotely simmilar makes me want to have it immediately. It handles very easely. This game have not glitched on me yet and I have played 40 hours so far. It is anoying though how fast you can die from one blow. But I guess thats why you have all the stealth powers and ability to be invisible lurking in the darkness. When I bought this game, I didn't look when it was published. I usually have a rule not to buy anything older than 2015 even if on sale. But this was very cheap, so I got it and I don't regret it to be honest. I reccomend it to everyone who loves Assassins, however wants to play fantasy instead. Who still has a bit of love for elves and goblins, likes cursing a lot and enjoys when a character can drop an \"f-bomb\" on you here and there. Styx is definately is one of my fav characters nowadays. And its hard to make that list for sure.", "appid": "242640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198045682840", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545048000.0}
