{"text": "Boardlands: The Pre-Sequel. A game that I was excited to play and bought out right once it was pre-ordered. Boy was I let down. Let's just point them out in power point fashion! YEAH! 1. Character balance which there is none because Nishas' ability is ridiculously over-powered with strong guns. (Come on a Machine Gun Sniper Rifle how original?) 2. Weapon Balance despite having played all of the borderlands the weapons were like shooting peashooters than actual guns. Most of the time the enemies would have better weapons then you. Also having played with a co-op friend Who in my opinion is an awesome gamer. Both of us combined were not enough to stop going down in the first five minutes of the game. 3. We died so fast to elemental damage that no matter how much you tried to put on the right kinds of shields the enemy would break them faster than a condom. 4. It costs too much for rocket ammo I had to sell my whole inventory just to get a few shots which is more to say then some boys am I right? 5. The vehicles though fun at first the moon buggy became annoying to say the least because you would die off the most random cliffs. People might say, \"Hey don't drive off those cliffs.\" the steering is like having someone say \"here drive my vehicle it has power steering! Also, the wheel cranked up on 10 so that the only option was to go straight. Kind of makes me want to drive off those cliffs more... 6. Most guns were worthless that is why there is a mission for a grinder so that you are supposed to be environmentally friendly like Australia. 7. The Aussie jokes were too much and were cultural. In fact they were so cultural specific that most of my American friends were scratching their head and saying \"WTF why am I playing this still.\" 8. There is not enough gore to satisfy my gore pleasure because... Australia. 9. Aussie will never be able to explain a Billabong to an American because it is not a brand of clothing it is an oxbow lake. 10. Pre-Sequel would've been more fun if there was not the cheap gimmicks and recycled stuff from the other borderlands games. Thank God, it is an in between game and it is not Borderlands 3. #Billabong for size. #Here is a didgeridoo. 11. The game is only fun if you're Australian. Handsome Jack's quips only showed up twice in my 10 hours of game play time. He needed to show up more because the writers said \"THIS IS ABOUT HIM!!?!!?! AND HIS TEAM!?!!?!\" WTF!? 2k Austria WTF!?!?  (Yes, I wrote their oceanic continent wrong). 12. Enjoy your wallaby and wombats! They are probably enjoy our hard earned money for their preserves.", "appid": "261640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028219938", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1414584000.0}
