{"text": "8 years... Buying this game was automatic. What does this game feel like? Honestly? A Warband remaster with improved graphics. Early Access I'm sure some things will improve and be added, but do I think the end product will be worth the wait and hopes and dreams? No... No I do not. EDIT: Later in game, as of patch 3, the crashes are so frequent doing sieges it's almost impossible to play atm. But they are patching consistantly. EDIT: Patch 5, I crash every time I try to save lol. EDIT: Patch 8 fixed my siege crash, and is playable now. More random crashes but I have advanced quite a bit. Stable enough to have some fun now.  EDIT: Patch 10: Well, I can play, I guess that's a plus. But these lords come back, even from long defunct kingdoms. You can never vanquish anyone... I started executing them... and more come under different names. I give up. EDIT: Patch 1.1: Game was steadily improving, to the point you could play without very frequent crashes, but I lost all sound in the game. Sigh. EDIT: Patch 1.1.1: Have sound again. Things seem stable. They are patching at a good rate and have a good alpha/beta/release system. They are going in the right direction.", "appid": "261550", "steamid": "profiles/76561197961038549", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1585656000.0}
