{"text": "I like to play point and click games from time to time and \"Beyond This Side\" seemed interesting because of the original art style. The graphics appear to be handdrawn and have a nice aesthetic to them. It's one of the game's only strong points. However, it's not like you haven't seen it before. The visuals aren't mindblowing or refreshing. Having played the first two episodes, I'm not sure if I'm going to play the third when it's released. The story barely kept me interested throughout the first episode. They tried to add some mystery towards the end of episode 2, but unfortunately failed miserably. The ending was nothing more than a letdown and definitely doesn't invite the player to buy the last episode. The excessive amounts of text (in Comic Sans, mind you) make the game feel extremely slow and sluggish. The meaning of this is probably to draw you into the universe of 'Beyond This Side' and to flesh out the characters, but all you're getting is mundane information that only bores the living hell out of you. It keeps dragging on...  I couldn't care less which movie the girl liked as a teenager or that her bookshelf will probably collapse in the near future. Some games can draw you into their world with this kind of info, \"Beyond This Side\" clearly could not.  Besides that, I didnâ€™t find the puzzles particularly engaging. Most of them are either too easy, reliant on trial and error, or a couple of tedious tile-sliding puzzles that are almost exactly the same. In other words, not fun or innovative. They add nothing to the story or aren't remotely related to it. And again: they are nothing you haven't seen before.  If that wasn't enough, you have to do the same lackluster puzzles multiple times throughout the game. Reconstructing photos, moving junk around to find a camera, sliding blocks in their designated slots. They aren't fun the first, but the third time you'll be really glad they added a SKIP button.", "appid": "1254480", "steamid": "profiles/76561197995403764", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602158400.0}
