{"text": "But THQ butchered this. Here are some points I noticed while playing: - Too many cutscenes! There were barely any in the original. - Character design: That's not nameless! - That is not Diego either; what happened to them both being thrown into prison and helping each other out? - It's so â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ bright! - It feels like everyone has suddenly turned talkative and happy. I remember in the original you were outcasts. - Nameless had an attitude in the original game, but not \"worst day ever\" - attitude. Fix it. - What the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ is that combat system? The original one was superb. - I could jump and climb and bug my way through the Gothic world. What happened to that?  - Please no invisible walls. Gothic was great because of that kind of freedom. - The saturation. Gothic was grey and dark, the atmosphere fit perfectly. Not bright & shiny like Fallout 4. - Too many skeletons and human-build stuff in the mines. They were empty and left for good in the original. - The dialouge system was perfect...why change it to garbage? - First 20 Minutes of the game: Cutscenes and WAY too long dialogues. What happened to the short / skippy dialouges? -  Now to the stuff that I do like: + That fighting stance! Oh how I remember looking like a 5 year old who just picked up a stick. Nice touch bringing it back! + â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ finally a game that gets the shealth right. Swords don't float in midair. + I like the attempt to bring Gothic back for good.  So much has changed and change is supposed to be good. But not in this case.  If THQ continues to develop this remake the way they are aiming at now, it will fail horribly. I want Gothic. Pure Atmosphere, story, the freedom to go & do anything.  Not Rise + Elex.", "appid": "950670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198069208364", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576238400.0}
