{"text": "Rogue Party 2 is an indie, 3D third person rogue-lite dungeon crawler. While it is not the worst thing i played, it is mediocre at best. Art approach is low-poly and sound effects are mishmash of low and decent quality of nonsense. While UI does its' job, it is really ugly. It seems like developer of this game tried to avoid some artwork usage (like icons, images etc) and i couldn't understand the reason of that. Only thing you can see in-game as image is mana and health icons which reminds me of my old attempts to create something decent on mspaint. Ah, there is also the parchment image (clip art) you see when you unlock an achievement or an item. Gameplay-wise, combat is dull. There is no melee combat since you throw your weapons. AI is poor. There is no free look and trajectory logic is same as most of FPS games of 90's. Inventory system is basic. When you grab an armor, weapon or magic item from a chest, it immediately replaces your equipment with the one you got. There is no way to reverse this process since your previous equipment vanish. Also, you can't compare your equipment to the item you found in chest before you change it. While you can learn the quality of items throughout your play time, there is no way to really know if your currently equipped and upgraded item is inferior or superior to item you found in a chest. Maybe inventory screen will help. I don't know why the developer made a so-called sequel to first Rogue Party. It seemed to me that he could improve the first one without releasing the second. If you compare Rogue Party to Rogue Party 2, you can see that they are identical. I didn't try to play the game co-op so i can't comment on that. TL;DR: There are far better alternatives to this game. First thing comes to my mind is Barony.", "appid": "1274980", "steamid": "profiles/76561197981055338", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592827200.0}
