{"text": "After I completed SUPERHOT and unlocked every achievement all I wanted was SUPERHOT 2 with same concept just with more levels, more possibilities, more weapon, more of everything just implemented as same as in original game. Instead we got SUPERHOT MIND CONTROL DELETE - a procedurally generated mess. To be honest, I partially got what I wanted: more levels, more enemies more weapons and more posibilities. The problem is, they were delivered in such a way that I lost fun and interest in game after first 2 hours and continued to play to see what content the game has, whats there after the end and for unlocking achievements.  The biggest problem of the game is it is fully RNG based what I really hate in games. Everything but placement of weapons and objects on levels is RNG. Damn, even order of levels themselves is RNG.  To provide some context, game uses rogue-like structure: you have 'Nodes' which contain 10+ levels (there are about 30+ levels and each node mixes 10+ of them and in case of death, game changes the maps and their order), each level has RNG amount and variety of enemies.  Due to RNG nature of Nodes I didnt enjoy maps as they were getting freaking repetative and I didnt have chance to get used to them because you always getting pushed by enemies so I ended up with jumping around the maps like bitten by bee in the ass. Speaking about enemies, MIND CONTROL DELETE introduces 3 invincible enemies which cant be killed or stunned so player should keep distance from them while trying not to get killed by plenty of other enemies. I didnt have that much problems with first 2 of them but the last one,damn, the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ always spawns with weapons and because it cant be stunned game turned into \"matrix simulator\", sweating trying to avoid bullets while also keeping an eye on other enemies. If devs call it challenge then I strongly disagree, RNG based games are not challenging they are annoying. Game also introduces new abilities called Cores and Hacks. Cores are essentially Hacks with one exception: they work throughout the Node while Hacks are given 2 or 3 times and you have to choose between 2 of them and when player completes the Node game just resets choosen Core and Hacks and this is the first problem. The second problem is, due to again RNG system player simply cant experiment with different combos of hacks because you just choose from 2 of hacks given by the game. I would fully enjoy all these new hacks and cores if they were implented in seperate \"Challenges\" mode as in original SUPERHOT. After you complete all the nodes you have to wait 2:30 hours (changed from 8 hours in latest update) in order to fully complete the game and all you get is PURE.core (1 hp, no hacks, no cores). I wonder how masochist you should be to use this core in MIND CONTROL DELETE because game simply isnt designed for the gameplay of original SUPERHOT, at least 2 hp is needed.  Game is overall not rewarding at all. You get â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ Core for waiting 2:30 hours, you get small portion of \"lore\" for beating '100 Node'  and so on, just useless â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. I could write more about my complaints in detail, but that would be even longer post.  I do not recommend this game even during sales, better pass and hope for true sequel which isnt â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ up as SUPERHOT MIND CONTROL DELETE.", "appid": "690040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198125197284", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595419200.0}
