{"text": "Left 4 Dead 2 is sequel of the Left 4 Dead game. Whats new: Survivors. Now we can choose between Nick (an ex-prisoner who escaped in the wake of the Infection), Ellis (a mechanic hailing from Savannah), Coach (Physical Education teacher at the local high school) and Rochelle (a minor associate producer for a news station) Special Infected. The Charger, The Jockey and The Spitter. Their characteristics bring new challenge for survivors skills. New weapons. P220 & Glock, Magnum (Deagle), Chrome shotgun (better accuracy than a Pump one), Silenced SMG (better damage than UZI), Ak-47, SCAR, SPAS (Combat shotgun), and a Military Rifle. A whole bunch of melee weapons. New items. Bile Jar, Adrenaline and Defibrilator. New Game Modes. Also there has been added Steam Workshop to this game. So now a player can download a custom file to change game files in-game. _______________________________________________ Replayable: Yes Interesting plot: No Singularity: Yes Gameplay 7 of 10 Graphics 6 of 10 P.S. Really poor animation in-game that can only be fixed with an addons. In-game Sounds & Music 3 of 10 P.S. Gun sounds also are terrible. Interface and in-game controls 9 of 10 TOTAL 4 of 10 P.S. Out of time. P.S. In my honest opinion the game is a lot worse than original L4D.", "appid": "550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149336317", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1410436800.0}
