{"text": "The game was ok at start and followed a logic of checkpoints in case of a fail which it followed until the very end in which the checkpoint was right next to the gate instead of outside where the snow was, forcing me to end it without wanting to and explore that hall more. So because it didn't follow the safety logic until the end and made you force end the game without your volition I wanted to give it a 8/10 but won't, I give it a 6/10, that was something that ruined my experience of it and got me extremely annoyed by it doing that. In order to go back and do it you need to redo the whole game, no, I am uninstalling it right now and I hope the programmers fix such stupid rookies mistakes in the future. I mean come on, the real exit was like 20 meters ahead of you but you put the script to end the game and not allowing even a checkpoint in case the player wanted to explore more, now that's stupid and you should learn from that. An easy fix would be a confirmation to end the game too. That gate ending right as soon as you step out angered me extremely because I was returning back towards the hall too, just came around it to see if there is something on the other side. Won't be trying the second game because of that, unless it gets fixed, only then will I even consider it.", "appid": "582500", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975294582", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549108800.0}
{"text": "Interesting approach to an NSFW game; normally it would just be 'virtual fun' if you catch my meaning; however the real points go to the artistic design of the game. It is no joke when the game is inspired by Lovecraft and H.R. Giger because you can see & hear it everywhere in this prologue alone. HOWEVER; while i give points to the artistic design -- i give negative points to the gameplay; it's essentially fetch quests \"go do this\" \"do a puzzle\" etc, etc. You know how it goes. Depending on the price point in the full game is the huge factor; overall i say if you are curious then try it! However, do not be surprised how very little this prologue has to offer; obviously the full release is going to be different; but this does not warrant a full download P.S.  NO there is no NSFW option once completing the demo", "appid": "1170820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198068329619", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602936000.0}
