{"text": "Playing through Temple of Sun alone as sorcerer. Game balance is so bad that I cannot recommend this game to anyone. Enemies have way too much HP and bosses are just pure pain. I am struggling with the end game boss and it is not fun at all. Not even challenging fun. Just awful design. Here are its abilities: * Lots of HP. I guess in range of thousands. My regular attack does 12 points of damage. * It keeps spawning endless amount of ranged unit. * Every enemy in the level does fire damage so even if you get hit only once, it keeps burning you. * In each phase, boss gets new ability. In third phase, it gets tracking fire pillars. In fourth and last phase, it gets tracking fireballs. One hit from either pillar or ball will kill you because of extended fire damage. Unless you use potion but you only have one. So you have at maximum one hit before you die. * Best part: boss regenerates if you are outside of combat area. And it regens fast. If you die, it has gained all the damaged health back and likely even more. So extra lives are useless because you have to kill it without dying. I have over 25k gold that I cannot use because there are no upgrades left for sorcerer. Another messed up gameplay design flaw! Got through third phase by just kiting the boss in circular motion. This is the only way I found to survive. Unfortunately, each round only nets you couple hits so this took me perhaps 30 mins of kiting. Who finds this kind of gameplay fun or engaging? Did the dev even play the game and boss? Feels more like just hammering as much difficulty as one can without thinking.", "appid": "239070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004748172", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595246400.0}
