{"text": "A walking simulator where you wander around aimlessly looking for an exit to prompt yourself to the next world. Neither direction nor instructions given with no real incentive for progression. The only saving grace for Wanderlust would be its visuals, because under the hood what it conceals is rather unsettling.  - Shamelessly lowkey advocating the use of (SAM) Steam Achievement Manager for the only achievement available with no other unlockable method? - Around half an hour or less of play time for 8 bucks? - Un-optimized textures and copy-pasted assets? - No Trading Cards since its release in 2017 though indicated on Steam page? - Misleading specs? 50 megabytes indicated but actually 6.15 gigabytes? - Usage of supposedly copy-righted music? Wanderlust is fraudulent and should be removed unless any justification for those points are brought forth.  *", "appid": "729670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198279621511", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "23", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563537600.0}
