{"text": "This game will not challenge you, ever, even at the hardest difficulty. RotTR is extremely easy. Everywhere you have this white paint to signal where you can jump. Lara also has a peculiar \"sense\" where you click Q and all interactive objects in the area will be highlighted for you. She also has plenty weapons and ammos since the beginning. You can clear rooms with 5+ enemies in an instant, and without much challenge. And again, this is straight from the beginning, and at the hardest difficulty setting. Never seen a game underestimate players ability this much. The game is also as linear as they make them, with entire sections that are completely on rails. What really drove me to the point of feeling frustrated while playing is the fact that all areas are stuffed to nausea with these small interactive objects. They range from crafting ingredients to relics, but the only thing you can do is go near one and click the action button, and that's it. Hundreds of times per area (and these levels aren't that big either). Lara will mumble a random line, and your \"level completeness counter\" will go +1. That's it. There is also zero thought behind how these items are placed around, you will find pieces of maps, or boxes in the middle of a bush, or on top of a tree. There is no balance at all either, so after one or two areas Lara will be full on many of these crafting ingredients. The famous tombs from the franchise name are optional! They are irrelevant to the story and game, can be skipped, and even if you do them they will give basically nothing! I would like to give a trophy to that employee that thought a good idea to make tombs irrelevant in a tomb raider game. Cherry on top, this title has microtransactions. Seems like they are for multiplayer only, but you earn microtransaction related credits during the single player. And always during the single player campaign you will be prompted to go check the marketplace menu, and buy some pointless cards not meant for the single player. There was a beautiful game underneath all this manure, but they just killed it. To me is absolutely baffling how this game can have such a high rating.", "appid": "391220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082258384", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1536580800.0}
