{"text": "I had high hopes for this game, but what the community said was entirely true: The map is glitchy, unfinished and you can even walk through walls and clip through the ground. It ruins the immersion and it's also infuriating to realize that they could have easily fixed this in an update. Gameplay mechanics remain unpolished and it doesn't feel like a survival game at all. The enemies would have been interesting to fight if the environment hadn't been so buggy and lazily made. Weapons, especially firearms, feel underpowered and not satisfying to use. The gunplay is one of the most terrible examples I have ever experienced in a video game. These are only a small percentage of a hundred more reasons I can give.  Don't buy this.", "appid": "247730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100114741", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1494590400.0}
