{"text": "I bought this game end of October and I was quite impressed with it. But after playing it for 500 hours it's somewhat important to write a follow-up after getting some experience. So, here's my first, early access review:  \"After playing this game for over 80 hours, I can say it's quite infectious and addictive. The game is flawed, the optimization is awful and BattlEye cheat detection isn't perfect, but overall it's a game with an original idea and is worth playing and is worth your 30 dollars.\" And today, end of February I can say that there is more bs from devs, more cheaters and less useful updates. We're getting useless cases nobody asked for, like the Militia and Fever crates. Why aren't we getting more bans. A few days ago I got teamkilled by a Chinese guy because I had a supressed AWM. I check his op.gg and even after my report, he's still playing like nothing happened. Also, a guy fires 20 bullets at me with a SCAR-L from over 200 meters with a 4x, and even after my cheating report, he's still playing. Why aren't you doing anything about the reports Bluehole? Where's our region lock so we can block out players that have a desync and high ping advantage? Am I paying this much for my 250 mbps internet to get killed by a asian cheater in PUBG? F-ck you Bluehole and Brendan Greene for even trying to blame the players and not the cheaters and arseholes. When we get a region lock, I'll consider giving the game a positive review.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198286146448", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1512216000.0}
