{"text": "Has as much content as the first Monster Hunter from over a decade ago.  Get MHO which is free and has an english patch (also has better textures and uses Cryengine3), or get a Switch and GenU. They have way more content and with the differ weapon styles and arts it's like having 5x more weapons to choose from. (Styles are differ ways you can wield the weapons. Providing new combos and maneuvers) This game looks great, plays smooth, but within a week you'll have killed all 30 monsters twice, once on normal and again on hard and you'll be done. Unless you get sucked into grinding the same stuff to find jewels (Jewels go into sockets on your weapons and armor and they're random drops after a hunt). It's like the end game of any Diablo. Grind loot so you can grind loot.  The other recent MH games have like 3 times as many monsters, higher tiers of weapons, higher difficulty levels, and wayyyy more weapons and armor in general.  Most all the issues and bugs have been taken care of within the first month. Only thing I know of now is the complaint about low res textures and a bug that causes your character to stutter and slow down during aim mode with a ranged weapon while using mouse & keyboard.  (While in aim mode with a ranged weapon if you strafe to the side while moving your mouse left or right your character will stutter and slow to like half speed. << To me that's game breaking if you prefer mouse & keyboard. Luckily I don't) It's shocking that it hasn't been fixed and it happens to everyone.  If you REALLY wanna try it I'd say try to find it for $40 at most.", "appid": "582010", "steamid": "profiles/76561197971088364", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1535198400.0}
