{"text": "Superhot is a really innovative new shooter that does a lot to immerse you in the world it creates around itself. It is extremely fun to play around with, and can certainly be a game you can play with friends to see who can do the coolest things, but $25 is a bit too much for what is being bought. For one, Superhot's main story is only about 2 hours long. Even with a dozen retries on some levels, I still completed it in under 2 hours. That is quite ridiculous, as the replayable content doesn't go very far after that either. The only modes available following the main story are Endless Mode and some Challenge modes. You can probably squeeze a few extra hours out of those if you're in love with the game, but other than that... you won't be playing this for long, and as such, you definitely won't want to cough up $25 for a 3-4 hour experience in a video game. Is Superhot worth playing? Yes. Like I said, it is exhilarating to play. It's an experience I've never had before, and would love to have again in a different aesthetic. Maybe a more realistic one. If you can buy Superhot on sale, go for it. But at it's current asking price, I just can't recommend the title.", "appid": "322500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198011242890", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "153", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1456488000.0}
