{"text": "I'm tending to the PvE fraction, which was the key aspect for me to dive into LoA. There's only one PvP region at the moment, most of the regions/towns/settlemets are PvE. Straight to the point for my thumb down: The economy isn't working, seems unbalanced due to the lack of transparency. I can only guess why, but it feels to me that the possibility to sell stuff directly by house owners instead of using an auction house / market place is doing no good. Travelling around comparing lots of merchants (the hired house owner NPCs who sell stuff) is another time sink. Thus forces you to have your available char slots used to do each and any crafting job for your own, slowing the IG economy even more down. Next massive time sink. House building, if you're able to secure your own plot of land first, is very very expensive. In terms of play time for harvesting materials, to have enough coins to buy a blue print plus your plot of land too. Regular taxes not included which will force you to do the grind part even more intensely. Without your own plot of land you cannot sell stuff (loot or self-built items). Crafting quests to get you new receipts and some coin are time guzzlers beyond compare. You can see hordes of farming chars in the woods or mines to do the same action for (RL) hours or even days. Newbies get overrun by older chars by pure load capacity, just check an caravan of pack horses following one char. Taming? You've to 'call' commands via chat for each action like follow, defend or whatever. Your beasts feel weak compared to warriors or mages. You're no glass cannon in the slightes expect you have maxed out your taming skill and own one pet which is worth taming for farming. And last but not least the 'new' premium subs. I feel bad about it. I bought LoA because it was F2P. A few weeks later they switched to subs. Personally I feel cheated. Sure, you don't have to do so but w/o you'll miss stuff in game (key aspects). Sorry, to me LoA is a waste of time and money in its current state.", "appid": "594770", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007173692", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1569153600.0}
