{"text": "I more and more feel like this game is going downhill: - From a technical point of view the game is a mess and probably will always be. Even with my 6800k 6c/12t processor and 1080ti graphics card the game puts much stress on the hardware. The graphics simply do not justify that. With older hardware many people struggle to get the game running decently. Aiming (compared to cs) feels slow and sluggish if you don't turn down the settings. - Rather than fixing the game, devs seem to care more about cosmetics and dlc's. - The amount of cheaters increased over the time. At least they TRY to do something against it. - hitboxes couldn't be worse. - Skin cases have ridiculous low drop rates for high tier items. - Bad connection / servers - definitely NOT e-sport ready (became a meme already) - the devs are changing thing in the game just for the purpose of changing them, not because it makes any sense. 5 different grips? Seriously? Constant recoil changes, damage changes that are unnecessary most of the time. - Some weapons feel way to random, which can mostly be explained with bad hitboxes and servers. The only pro right now is that you do not end up as a fortnite kid when playing this game.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198168423186", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "20", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530360000.0}
