{"text": "DooM Eternal is a bit of a disappointment. Between a bit heavy handed gameplay, unreliable always online drm and a big collectathon i don't think this game is worth it's asking price. (Especially not with the dlc.) What i'm missing is the thing that made DooM 2016 good/fun. An arcade mode that skips the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. The soundtrack is amazing and always fits very well to what is currently happening in game and i hope we will be able to buy it standalone soon. The graphics are very good and good looking albeit a bit generic knight/viking levels were added and the hell aesthetics aren't that gritty anymore. (compared to 2016) Gameplay feels more like a character action game (like dmc e.g.) in first person than a shooter. Movement got upgraded with dashes and a grappling hook on the ssg (yay :D) but this is needed since normal movement is pretty much only useful out of combat to get you to the next fight. In combat you jump, dash and monkey bar swing away from demons in enclosed arenas where you are expected to dispose every enemy according to it's assigned way. If you happen to not utilise the enemies gimmick/weakness they are very bullet spongey which you can't afford them to be because ammo is intentionally scarce and you have to rely on the fodder enemies as your resource (health/armor/ammo) batteries. I have a feeling they mistook action with being stressed and just added more mechanics (aka stuff to worry about) on top until the right level of stress was reached. The progression system is awful and annoying. Almost everything that makes combat a bit more fun is locked behind a progress bar or point system. The first hours of this game is work to get to the fun and strongly reminds me of game design that wants to push you to paying money to avoid the grind. I mean to improve a weapon you have to find a drone to unlock a specialisation first. Then get weapon points to improve it and unlock the mastery and then do a challenge to really unlock the mastery which you can skip by paying another kind of token. You have to do this twice for every weapon and a similar system is in place for the suit and health/armor/ammo upgrades. Did i mention the weapon you have to unlock by collecting keys through completing challenges and the batteries you have to collect to unlock skins or other unlock currency? But when you have worked through the annoying/awful things the game is quite fun. Alas not as fun as the hype bros want to make you believe. Edit: (I forgot to mention the issues with  When you are starting the game or loading a level or just open the codex/arsenal ingame menu with tab the game wants to connect to  . If the service is not reachable or slow you are forced to wait a long time through the connect attempt without the ability to abort.", "appid": "782330", "steamid": "profiles/76561197960710753", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585483200.0}
