{"text": "Ok so I dont usually write reviews but this needed to be addressed, I got preorder access to the beta which was up for only a couple of days load times were up to 15mins long just getting to multiplayer and despite numerous performance issues halfway through multiplayer the person I qued up with would run in place and disconnect. Now I know what your thinking why am I saying this? The beta was just a test right? The game has to be fleshed out and in good condition now? Wrong. I love the 40k universe to deathwing (Had to) but the multiplayer is just as broken load times are a tiny bit better still too long for a high end gaming pc running the game at ultra getting over 60fps; the single player is just as bad I get a little bit further everytime but inevitably I freeze and crash i believe its a graphics issue or audio bug due to direct X11 not recognising my card which is really odd. The devs had more than enough time to fix this especially with the extended wait time for launch but they did not address it. I definetley do not recommend buying this unless you want crash simulator. However if the devs resolve this issue I will remove this negative review until then. 10/1000000 would not buy crash simulator 2016 again.", "appid": "298900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052265340", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1481889600.0}
