{"text": "First off, let me say I have played L.A. Noire before on other platforms and absolutely loved it. It is truly a one of a kind game and if you own a console you should definitely play it. As for the PC version, it seems due to a series of updates to WIndows 10 that the game is broken now. In my experience, I would hit launch game on the menu and it would begin to load up, but then crash soon after that. I have tried all the different fixes I could find and none of them have worked for me, and as far as I know Rockstar isn't planning on fixing the issue completely anytime soon. I know some people have been able to fix the game, but unfortunately, I wasn't able to. If you are able to get this game to work, it is an unforgettable experience. Feel free to comment below if you have any fixes I may have missed, and if it works I will happily change this review.", "appid": "110800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198093830694", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533038400.0}
