{"text": "is the dictionary definition of \"Asset Flip.\" The experience is laughably short, comprised of just two 3-minute missions, has the most basic A.I. imaginable, and is inhabited by barely altered low poly models seen in far too many games already overpopulating Steam. I'm not even going to bother to do my usual Pro/Con breakdown, this isn't a game, it's barely even a tech demo. I'll give the developer credit that the first stage environment is visually interesting, but that's as far as it goes. The castle stage has a far more fun-looking town just north of your spawn point, but it's devoid of life, and no structures can be entered. Everything is window dressing to hide the fact that the game has zero substance. Enemies are dumb as a rock, capable of only the most basic attack. Apparently, if you hit several in close proximity, they will start to turn on each other until only one is left standing. Is this an intentional feature? Whatever the case, it trivializes the game's already anemic difficulty. Stage 2 has you climbing castle walls, but this mechanic only works when standing on giant \"climb\" buttons which vanish after use. Once you reach the holding cell of your fellow tribeswomen, the game abruptly ends. I'm not sure if there is a legitimate way to enter the cell other than from above... I kept swinging a sword until I clipped through the gate by accident. And finally,   doesn't even deserve the Hentai in its title, obviously added for sales effect. Nudity in this game is equivalent to looking at a Barbie doll. What's the point of being able to toggle clothes in the first place when you can already see through their revealing leaf coverings? For collectors only. Consider this game at risk for removal, should Valve QC decide to start doing their job. : Extremely easy. Complete both stages, double click the nude option in the main menu. You're done in under 10 minutes if you don't explore.", "appid": "1248970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198219343843", 