{"text": "I had my eye on Chaosbane for some time as both a fan of Diablo-style ARPGs and Warhammer, but passed over it at launch and thereafter due to is very mixed reception. I heard about the upcoming added Witch Hunter class and was motivated to finally take the plunge. Having now tried it at a sale price, I can say it's not really my thing, and that is disappointing. I do like the game, but it didn't grab me like an ARPG ought to. By all means try it for yourself, especially if you have someone to try the local coop with. I expected a situation where the beginning gameplay would be entertaining and that if I stuck with it I would encounter the dearth of endgame content so often referred to in other reviews, but as you can see from my play time I obviously did not get that far. I cannot pinpoint what about Chaosbane turned me off other then the general slowness of the combat flow, but 40k Inquisitor also has this and that in of itself did not kill that game or this one for me. There is just something... off about Chaosbane's basic gameplay. It made me want to go play either Vermintide 2 or a different ARPG. Chaosbane seems competently designed, taking several mechanical cues from Diablo 3 that kept me playing that game for so long: recharging health potion, a range of AoE and movement skills, easily redistributed skill allocations, et cetera. The basics are there, but the X factor is not. It lacks the charm and mod support of Torchlight 2, the audio/visual flair and breakneck combat pace of Diablo 3 or the oomph and diverse character builds of Grim Dawn.  I must say I am impressed that it has a local coop option, and that alone almost made me decide to keep the game, but it's hard getting even one other person to play these sorts of games with me. It wouldn't be the first time I enjoyed a game in coop that I didn't alone. I would be willing to try Chaosbane again somewhere down the line if I heard it made some improvements to its formula.", "appid": "774241", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970739339", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "51", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603972800.0}
