{"text": "So!, i've beaten the game as of writing this Review. I've been a Amnesia Fan for YEARS Especially - Amnesia: The Dark Descent A Machine for Pigs was an alright Amnesia game. Either way this review is about - Amnesia: Rebirth ---------------------------------------------- I'm gonna be honest it did not feel like a \" Amnesia \" game. It felt more like a Outlast game.. But with a touch of Sci-Fi - Space stuff. It just.... didn't feel like a Amnesia game if im going to be Honest. It had some aspect of Amnesia: The Dark Descent Which felt nice seeing. Quality was / is -  awesome. Atmosphere - It's awesome if you like Alien Technology. I think it was an Alright game. As i was going in thinking that it would be really familiar to the previous 2 games. But then a Alien world appeared, it kinda put me off. I did jump now and then, in the Fortress. The Fortress had some nice Jump scares, i give the game that. But seeing that The game only has 2 kind of Monsters in it is kind of a Downer. (Ghouls - Spectral) You easily got used to the 2 Monsters, which made it less scary to future encounters. ---------------------------------------------- That being said, let's wrap it up. I give the game a  5.5 / 10.", "appid": "999220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198320422220", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603281600.0}
