{"text": "Honestly, I'm so sad I don't like it. I've been playing TW since Rome and ammased too many hours on them: ROME: 1000+ (all on disk - recently bought in on steam) Medieval 2: 1500+ (all on disk - also bought on steam) Empire: 130+ (and about 200 more on other accounts and offline which never seemed to be added to my hours until last year Â¯\\_(ãƒ„)_/Â¯ ) Napoleon: 45+ Rome 2: 235+ Attila: 20+ Warhammer: 2  And I was hyped for this game. Finally TW is back with historical campaigns!!! But alas it's another let down. Since Rome 2 I feel the quality has dropped so far, Warhammer was, for me, terrible. I never understood the Warhammer battle mechanics, flying units and magic, it felt out of place for a Total War game, and this feels similar.  The campaign is sort of clunkyand somewhat \"bland\". Also there are no city garrisons, unless I was doing something wrong.   To top that off my favourite part of Total War... The battles... They don't last anywhere near long enough, I was fighting against a West Seaxon (West Seax?) army and I had more advanced units and more units, as soon as 30 men died in a unit they fled, no matter what, if they were mine or the enemys', I play on very hard battle difficulty so im used to a bit of wavering but they all flat out ran away and didnt rejoin, I won the battle but it didn't feel like a Total War battle.  I could go into more detail but no one will read it so I'll stop here.", "appid": "712100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033844606", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525780800.0}
