{"text": "EDIT: With more hours played now I have to say im still sticking with my original review. To the common player this game will get boring fast. But overall its fun. Fall Guys is an ok game. I honestly enjoy the game and believe the general audience will aswell especially if your'e a younger player BUT I feel that this game will get boring very fast....unless the developers continue adding content and improving their game. Fall Guys is a great concept and has amazing art style/audio. They could have done without the \"Battle Pass\" thing that Fortnite has but oh well. Hopefully they will continue work on this game and its not a quick cash grab. Overall I give the game a 6.5/10", "appid": "1097150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198317451910", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596542400.0}
{"text": "Honestly, as savage as it sounds, the truth hurts, but Ubisoft has gotten LAZY. They no longer put in the extra effort and time to perfect their games as they have with the older titles. They used to settle for exceptional games, but nowadays they aim for just â€˜okay.â€™ Whereas they used to focus on experience and immersion, today itâ€™s more tailored towards money and making the series a franchise of multimedia. Too many careless and reckless bugs/mistakes in their games nowadays unfortunately. Too much copy paste, too much idle banter and grindy tasks. In my opinion, this particularly applies to Ubisoft Quebec, Both Syndicate and Odyssey, despite being fun solid games, are pretty much forgettable and donâ€™t bring forth anything memorable or extraordinary. Both Syndicate and Odyssey lack a serious tone and include too many cringe jokes and unnecessary tasks, which evidently are forgettable and dismissible. The other games made by different developers take it more seriously, and are often better in story, gameplay, and direction. Iâ€™m sure they mean well, and by all means their optimization is superior in terms of balance and performance, as both Syndicate and Odyssey performed smoother than their previous title. Also provide beautiful worlds such as the UK and Greece. I suppose Ubisoft should really figure out each of their different branches and their cons and pros and address them accordingly. I donâ€™t like Quebecâ€™s direction or narrative divisions, but appreciate and admire their graphics and stability department.", "appid": "812140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034686389", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592913600.0}
