{"text": "I've somewhat always enjoyed a good session of TD. and by the looks of it. This game thoroughly looks and even feels like an oldschool topdown towerdefense with your regular gun, rocket, lightning, fire, slowing, concussion/aoe towers and so on with varying maps and difficulties. However, the problem with this game is that you can clearly see it's made and it's meant to be in the marketplaces with microtransactions such as microsoft store and mobile devices where you can buy coins (Didn't know this when i purchased the game). And even when the developer has lowered the difficulty (According to his own words), the difficulty spike shows, and the maps become absolute pain to complete, especially if you want to get the related achievements (Completing the maps without losing a single life.) When you have to actually struggle through what's the halfway of the game at the time of the review on easy difficulty, you can imagine how hard this games hard or nightmare difficulties are.  Game lacks some serious optimization for it to be worth noted as a decent tower defense, but don't get me wrong, the gameplay itself is your generic towerdefense strategy which from time to time isn't bad, and didn't expect too much more for the admission of the game, however, i can't recommend the game to anyone until the serious optimization in difficulty/obtaining money to improve your towers are fixed. Especially when the levels themselves can take upwards of an hour even when sped up,. Oh and one final thing, completing the levels on harder difficulty won't attain you achievements for the lower difficulty levels, so you absolutely have to complete each level 4x in order to get the achievements.", "appid": "324520", "steamid": "profiles/76561197991757040", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592913600.0}
