{"text": "NOTICE: I am writing this review right after I have completed everything (100% sync). Unfortunately, I am not recommending this game. First, I don't like the idea which some misc items to be collected are hidden and we got to buy it, with real money if you want a shortcut. The story was not that good, in my opinion. Including side missions like Charles Darwin, Queen Victoria, etc. I think Ubisoft could've squeezed them into one mission instead of making 3-4 short missions. The graphics, however, I'm impressed, especially at night. It looks beautiful but not day time. The lighting feels and looks off. The next turnoff is the freaking glitch. There was once where I fell out from the map trying to open chests (check my screenshot). Another occasion was when I glitched into a building. Not to mention the soundtrack. The soundtrack was bloody good but it was not put up to good use. I felt boring exploring the city without the soundtrack playing in the background, in contrast to Assassin's Creed IV: Black Flag. Even on killing the enemies and sneaking into a hostile base. In my opinion, the cons outweigh the pros.", "appid": "368500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198166286884", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "19", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588852800.0}
