{"text": "I really wish I could pick between a thumbs up and down, because this game has potenial, constant updates, and passionate devs, but there are just so many bugs, systems, and components that if you are a new player and you don't have a friend to guide you, you will struggle, you will fail, and you will hate this game. The fact that rather than fix issues with texture collision, the devs descided to add an \"/unstuck\" command speaks for itself and I have yet to play a single game session without running into a bug. The tutorials are severally out of date, new features added are rarely explained propperly, and there almost seems to be a requirement to fail at least once before the game decides you might need an explaination that is still not comprehensive enough. I would have quit this game a long time ago if it were not for people guiding me through the many confusing bits, but honestly, if you are starting this game solo, good luck, because you are going to get overwhelmed as soon as you start. The worst part is the addition of the open worlds, which is usually something I would like since I love open worlds but the implementation of a host-based system means that if the host disconnects, you lose all of your progress. Imagine that in any other game: you spend hours doing activities and then the host decides to leave and thus you lose everything. at the very least, the devs could follow the method of gta online but with all of the bugs in this game I cannot recommend this game.", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198059095828", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1541937600.0}
