{"text": "Update, after 3 more Hours of Gameplay: The Pixel-Problems (Characters \"Cut in half\") are clearly most impactful on Feena. What's really positive is the Gamespeed when you're leveling, menuing, fighting or exploring - it makes the Game feel more enjoyable. Still, no thumbs up because of the graphical issues - will be a thumbs up if they at least TRY to fix it on a regular basis. Grandia is my favourite Game ever, but it has a lot to do with Nostalgia. I really looked forward to play it in the HD-Version, the Screenshots and Gameplay looked awesome. After the first 3.5 Hours of Gameplay i'm really disappointed...the Game itself is great, the Battle System and the Story is just as good as it was nearly 22 Years ago. BUT: In every little Cutscene there are Pixel-Bugs at the Character-Models (Characters seem \"Cut-in-half\"), Sound-Glitches still happen in some places (Battlestarts, strange Loops, etc.) and in some Scenes the Camera glitches out or the Scene isn't made for Widescreen (Opening Scene especially, Models staying on Screen when they shouldn't, etc.). Seriously, wasn't there any Playthroughs of the Game by Testgamers? I can't believe this. There are so many obvious flaws its ridicoulus. I'm very sad GungHo launched this Game in such a State. I'm no Fan of using Emulators, so i was more than willing to pay Money to get a new Version of this Masterpiece. In this State, especially if you're not as Nostalgic about the Game as the most of us - don't buy it.", "appid": "1034860", "steamid": "profiles/76561198026348154", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "81", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571227200.0}
