{"text": "This is a bad DLC, pure and simple which is a real shame because the previous one was quite good. Here are some of the reasons why I think it was sub-par: - Writing is just plain boring and it reminds me of the BL3 main campaign story which also sucked. I thought they were on the right track with previous DLC which actually had a pretty decent story but it's one step forwards and two steps back with these devs. - Levels are pretty average, there are a couple with cool visual design but the rest are mediocre. - Boring loot, having completed all side-quests, I have all the unique loot and it's meh at best, the legendaries specific to DLC are also sub-par and I won't be using them in my builds. - Really boring side mission design, it's just more \"kill enemies in designated circle\" and \"fetch this\" crap, out of all side missions only stood out. - Extremely poor endgame content, previous DLC had a number of areas that can be farmed for specific drops, world drops and XP, there is very little of that here. The story bosses are all multi-stage crap design that can't be farmed efficiently and all chests I opened just had garbage in them, not a single legendary. - It is short and lacking in content compared to previous DLC and BL2 DLC. - Extremely annoying achievements that add nothing of value to the game.", "appid": "1232257", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006217347", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "34", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585310400.0}
