{"text": "At first glance a nice game with nice elements. However, there is no catchy storyline and everything is the same from start to finish. Stupid shooting seems like the only goal, but finding hidden rooms and items is challenging! For those who like that and make no further demands, this might be a great game. Since everything is the same, it gets very boring halfway through so I no longer enjoy the gameplay. As a result, you simply sit down and shoot to finish the game as quickly as possible. The gameplay also offers a number of options to improve your performance and skins, but given the monotonous nature of the game and the boredom that it causes, it is not a challenge for me to work on it any longer. In short, for me a game that you play once and then never again.", "appid": "782330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198292029498", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "8", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597579200.0}
{"text": "I would avoid purchasing this game as it has very bare-bones gameplay at the moment. ==Pros == + Graphics are nice and colorful + The noises that the Mooj make when you pick them up remind me of Chao from Sonic Adventure. + The ability to skip directly to night time. + A variety of different features to enhance the garden including milking stations, farm areas and cooking pots.  + Mooj' appearance is based on their evolution from eating various food. == Cons == - First few days are very boring and hard to get into. - More emphasis is put on tower defense than simulation - you HAVE to fight monsters every night and defend the Mooj statue. - No music at all until random occasions such as an egg being produced or it switches to night. - Also, the music choice is very odd - it sounds like swing and big band music from the 40s and 50s that Dean Martin and Frank Sinatra would sing to. Very uncharacteristic. - The UI and text are difficult to read sometimes. Note: I didn't test what would happen if the Mooj statue lost all it's HP. I assume it's game over? I wish I waited to purchase this game and spent it on something else, but eh, you live and learn.", "appid": "1044760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090141267", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561550400.0}
