{"text": "Don't get me wrong. I think this could be a great game. The reason why I don't recomend it is because not only I think it should have achievements, but I think it should have like 200 of them... The mechanic of the game is to survive, you can't \"beat\" the game. And, in the end, is a game about \"doing things\". I think that the idea is great, but I also think that it would be nice to have some goals, and some way to know what you've managed to achieve... I know it has been asked many times, and developers said the reason why the game doesn't have achievements is mainly because they don't want to. I respect that, but they use to give some reasons that, to me, sounds more like excuses (I don't really know how hard is to add this to a game, programming and so...). But that is the reason I don't recomend this game. After a few hours, I'd rather be playing something else. If, unlike me, you don't care about that (Achievements, leaderboards...) then you might like the game. It is original, well designed and you can have fun playing it to kill some time.", "appid": "219740", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998124191", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1389096000.0}
