{"text": "A fun game with a great potential that is sadly absolutely hindered by some major issues (and I'm not even gonna bother with the high amount of interface and physics bugs): -The netcode is complete garbage, most often than not you get killed while running behind a wall or a door, thinking that you're safe, while in reality the bullet reaches you even as far as a couple of seconds after hiding; -Game is ravaged by hackers: from wallhacks to aimhacks and even no recoil, you name it. Most of them are coming from China, but for some reason ($$$), Bluehole still refuses to region lock it; -Certain features, such as vaulting or opening doors/picking up loot are slow and unresponsive, and in a battle royale scenario the speed of such actions can make the difference between life and death; The developers sadly seem more keen on adding unecessary features such as gun skins, emotes or more lootcrates than fixing major problems that ruin what could be an engaging experience. I played this game for a considerable amount of time so far and I would love to really like it, but Bluehole doesn't seem to care about a good playing experience as much as they seem to care about making a profit, so I can't commend them for that.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198130030967", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1523620800.0}
