{"text": "I'm really torn about this game. This game has a very interesting little story at its heart which will grab you if you give it the chance, but the overall game might not be worth your purchase (at least at full price). So lets break this down: The game starts with a relatively well animated intro with good music. The soundtrack is really good, at some points almost too good for the barebone nature of the gameplay. I like the artstyle of the game. The very cleanly drawn characters contrast well with the water-color painted backgrounds, altough on some screens this clashes a little too much. There are quite a few caveats though: This is a point and click adventure with puzzles so there are no suprises here. The puzzles are very reasonable and everything is very solvable by reading the text presented in the game. I enjoyed the puzzles because they were not frustrating but challenging enough to justify their existence. The point and click mechanics however, are disapointing. It is not very apparent where you character can move and it can be very frustrating to get your character from point A to B. The cursor will change to tell you where you can go, but sometimes the places where you can go are so needlessly small that it is hard to click them which results in some frustration. clicking on items from your inventory doesn't feel good and there is literally no feedback if you try to combine or use something, that you are not supposed to. There is actually still a bug in the game which freezes the game and the only way to procceed is to press the \"Skip\" button. So long after release you would've thought they might have fixed this. And even though I did not encounter a \"game breaking\" bug, there were quite a few instances of items just vanishing from the inventory (glad they were just invisible) or puzzles getting into undefined states. This game clearly lacks polish and I am surprised any decent game tester could overloock such obvious flaws. The story is what keeps this game afloat. It is a shame then, that this game is very short and the real plot is not revealed until 60~ minutes into the game, which is at about half of the play-time. Relating to the characters is hard when faced with not enough screen-time, but the themes the story is dealing with are heavy enough to make up for that. The Translations feels very clunky. I feel like there was a lot of missed opportunity to make the interaction between the cat and the heroine a lot more funny, which would've made the game a lot more enjoyable, especially in the beginning. I was also very disapointed about some key scenes in the story where I felt like I didn't quite get what was going on. All in all I'd say this game feels rushed. I really like the concept of the story and would like to see more of it, but the lack of polish, bugs, a slow start and the overall shortness of the game makes it hard to recommend this at full price. This game has a lot of unrealized potential.", "appid": "463460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198053670536", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1482667200.0}
{"text": "Antes de seÃ±alar las cosas malas de este juego quiero aclarar que aprecio que haya sido hecho con las mejores intenciones, este fue el primer juego de estos desarrolladores y ellos mismos admitieron que no fue bueno y bromeaban sobre ello, y usaron las crÃ­ticas para crear un nuevo juego lllamado OLDTV y segÃºn los anÃ¡lisis de Steam es muy buen juego, otra cosa que disfrute fue el trabajo puesto en las voces, se nota que pusieron mucho esfuerzo en eso. Pero desgraciadamente todo eso no elimina el hecho de este juego es terrible. Primero que nada, entiendo que no este en espaÃ±ol, pero que no hayan subtitulos ni siquiera en inglÃ©s complicÃ³ mucho las cosas, se bastante inglÃ©s pero aÃºn asÃ­ hay partes que no podÃ­a entender lo que decÃ­an por mucho que intentara. Y en cuanto a los niveles y rompecabezas en si, muchas veces busque guÃ­as sobre como pasar ciertas partes que aunque las pasara aÃºn no tenian sentido alguno. La historia en si es cualquier cosa, un chico llamado Antony va a una fiesta y despierta solo en una casa con un manÃ­aco que segÃºn Ã©l cree secuestro a su amiga Sam (La anfitriona de la fiesta), el manÃ­aco llamado Vinny te jode y grita todo el tiempo y tienes que escapar de Ã©l, por lo que entendi Vinny era un vendedor de drogas y Antony y Sam son hermanos y terminaron teniendo setzo en la fiesta y de eso se trata basicamente, sobre una fiesta que termino en incesto xddd. Una advertencia importante es tener cuidado al jugar este juego pues este juego me dio fuertes mareos y un dolor de cabeza jodido pues hay partes donde hay que escalar paredes y cosas asÃ­, muchisimas personas se quejaron de esto tambiÃ©n en los foros. AsÃ­ que bueno no lo recomiendo a menos que uses guÃ­as para pasarlo, es un juego hecho de manera sana y gratis, con logros fÃ¡ciles de conseguir y no dura mas de 2-3 horas, pero si no tienes paciencia puede ser un dolor de huevos.", "appid": "298260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198155496080", "voted_up": false, "votes_