{"text": "My heart beats for The Elder Scrolls series but... Bethesda, c'mon?  The Creation Club is a lack of respect for us, the players. There were mods better than the few in Creation Club, for the vanilla Skyrim.  Besides, you are trying to make more money on a 6 year old game instead of working on an Elder Scolls VII?? Give us something other than pay-to-play, please. Elder Scrolls Online was a complete fiasco for the people who have always loved the good old Oblivion, Morrowind and Daggerfall games (some like every single one - from Arena to Skyrim [me]).  I have over 20.000 hours in all Elder Scrolls games together (PC+Consoles) and as I watched Bethesda get bigger and bigger - they started caring less and less. And it shows in their games and pay-to-play spirit.  This isn't, sorry for the philosophical way this will sound, in the spirit of The Elder Scrolls. This is all money-making business, sadly. And we're not stupid - we can tell that THAT is what counts now. Money.  A young Cristopher Weaver once said \"the dream of gamers\" because Bethesda chased our dream - but... I don't know about you but paying 40 quid for a remake of a 6 year old game with paid mods to it - isn't my dream. Neither is a giant online game where it is clearly pay-to-play/ win.  Don't buy The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim Special Edition - it has nothing new or extraordinary to offer. You might as well buy the vanilla game and download free and amazing mods from Nexus. Edit:  And now they keep updating so the good old SKSE will not work for more than a few months at a time. It's sad seeing as how some of the newer Elder Scrolls games players/ modders brought on the foundation of most of the long-time players. No one would put so many hours into a game, without mods! Get your head out of your arse, Bethesda. The modders have been the ones keeping this dead ass game alive!", "appid": "489830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198111028550", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1507464000.0}
