{"text": "This is ensentially a slender game, a very buggy version I have to say. There tons of bugs but this is a free indie horror game so I can't hate. For example jump from a table down to the ground: \"You fell to your death\". Uh huh, killed my brained celss that's what happened. Same rules get pages, run away from Slenderman.  So, you're probably wondering where's the cool looking monsters in the trailer, hmmm... yeah there's none. It never came out, saying it did but no, no it didn't. Another thing I dislike is the map, not saying it's big, but the fact that you can get lost in the game.  The forest is dark and the flashlight the game gives you doesn't give enough light to see where you're going. There's one part where you have to climb this big a** tower just to save the game. Like seriously, I'd rather die from Slendy than climb that tower.  This game had potential but just never met the expectations of all gamers. All in all, if you want a scare you can get it, get it if you still fear the Slenderman. I give this game a 5.5/10", "appid": "241640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198147237442", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1420200000.0}
