{"text": "I have mixed feelings about this game.  The game can be an enjoyable WWII FPS experience.  However, there are several major items that cause the my friends and I to play other games in lieu of HLL on many occasions.   1) Most notably is the requirement that you stay the whole match to get any experience.  When you start a match, you're committed to the whole ride.  I don't know about your schedules, but I don't have 1+ hours stretches to commit. After playing for a bit, getting 30 kills, knocking out a few garrisons and ops... it really leaves a foul taste your mouth knowing you'll have to get off and have none of it count toward your character progression.  Oh, and If you're unlucky and it's your turn to crash, which happens often enough, say \"goodbye\" to your progression.  A lot of players, myself included would really like the developers to change this.   2) The server browser is lackluster to put it mildly.  Why can't we have filters where we can set an upper limit on ping, upper and lower limits on player count, select gamemode type, and have a list displayed of those servers? 3) Server Queuing.  What is the deal with this?  When the server list shows 85/100 players with 6/6 players in the queue... put them in the server already?  Why isn't the queue when the server is full?  Today, I waited in the queue several minutes to get into a server, when presented with the team selection screen, I find myself presented with player count on each time something like 42v42.  Why the hell did I sit here and wait for 5 minutes to get in?  There were 16 player spots available on the server. This is just irritating, especially when gaming time is a luxury. If the developers could change those things, it would certainly alleviate my annoyance with the game.  I have a good enough time playing the game.  The performance isn't too bad, graphics look pretty good, the game play pacing is good, the map size is just right, and finally the map development is pretty good with the environment feeling believable and conductive to good firefights. If you're cash strapped and wondering if you should get the game right now, I say...  No, wait to see if the developers fix the above items.  If you have plenty of time, cash, and WWII games are your thing, I say... maybe. Overall rating - 6.5/10 Rating if they fix issues noted above - 8.5/10", "appid": "686810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019696269", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1596974400.0}
