{"text": "I really wanted to like this game. I like 3D platformers, the likes of Spyro, Mario, and in a different way Sonic. But this game lost me quick. The combat is dismal, some of the time I have no idea what the character model is doing.  The platforming is not great either. the jump and double jump don't feel good, and is hard to control. Multiple times I got stuck on ledges and ropes, due to not being able to climb up or drop down.  The worst thing about this game though, is the voice acting. As you'd expect the story is the standard platformer fair, but the dialogue is painful, wih your charcter trying to be edgy. And of course Kay is voiced by a child, and sounds like a whinny brat. The only thing I thought was ok with the game was the artwork. It is a pretty game, but that can't turn me round on it", "appid": "313810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198074726148", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1488628800.0}
