{"text": "As a concept, the game is good... Now lets just actually discuss the game shall we? Softlocks the game is a first person Horror game with a plot that is somewhat so-so (Its understandable, but predictable), letting you explore a forest full of collision problems. If you buy this game, follow the paths, don't try to explore, weird right? you'd like trying to explore would help you find some hidden secrets? Or... Risk long sections of gameplay you've done just to get stuck on that Rock, Log, Small slope that looks traverseable and having to force a reset of the game, LOSING that progress (where most of my hours come from) Now, length, don't expect a long time if you avoided the dastardly hazards which are softlocks, because this game can span (In a long play session) roughly 3.5 - 4.0 hours, so if you think Â£24.99 (or whatever currency you use) is worth 4 hours of gameplay? then this would be the game for you. As of writing this i'm currently trying to get a refund, knowing my luck they will say \"No, you should have known this game was incomplete when buying\".", "appid": "1092660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048533035", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1567252800.0}
