{"text": "Good Christ I hate this game.  I wasn't expecting much out of a more modern shooter, but I had some hope given that it was done by the same developers of the legendary Aliens versus Predator PC game from 1999 (listed on Steam as Aliens versus Predator Classic 2000).  How foolish I was. Starting off with the Marine campaign, I'm given a taste of what to expect: slow and stiff movement, sub-par shooting mechanics, poor damage feedback (both to the enemy and to the player) - just everything of a first person shooter that tells me I should quit and go play something else.  But I hate myself and want to die so I was determined to play through it all. Everything about the Marine campaign pales to the 1999 classic.  Hard.  No tense atmosphere brought about by excellent lighting and level layout, and quick and deadly enemies.  No breakneck movement speed with lethal weaponry.  Just section after section of one tedious chore after another. Next up is the Predator campaign, which I think is the order they want you to play it in?  It went Marine -> Alien -> Predator in the '99 game, but whatever.  Again, the game is not as fluid and free as it was in AvP1999.  The targeting mechanism for both fighting and moving feels so restrictive.  It's almost a good idea, with the jumping ability of the Predator, but is hampered by requiring a pseudo lock-on system.  They also turned combat against the Aliens into some kind of first person brawler, with a light/heavy/block method.  Seriously. Now, they can take the tense Marine campaign and make it slow and tedious, and they can make the interesting and calculating Predator campaign and make it annoying and boring.  Surely they won't take the fun and clever Alien campaign and make it annoying and pointless, right? Why did I doubt this? Instead of moving around at lighting speed, preying on terrified humans as you hide in the shadows lining up a head bite, you... well, just like the other two campaigns, are moving slow as can be, are much less lethal, and have to engage in a combat system so boring it feels like it's all designed busywork - which I guess it is.  Easier than taking the time to design something that's actually fun.  I mean â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, there's a canned animation for entering vents!  For the ALIEN!  You have to press a button to enter a vent and there's an inescapable canned animation! Oh crap, I just realized I forgot to mention the grab system. So the Predator and Alien have a grab mechanic for instant kills.  Except it's not instant.  It's very, very slow.  And you're completely vulnerable during it.  Hey, that's good balancing, right?  Instant kill mechanic with a drawback?  Well, it makes them essentially pointless as you'd only do it when the target is alone, given how long it locks you into the canned animation each time.  Why even have this mechanic, then?  I guess to get around the game's other design fault of weaponry and attacks not being very lethal.  No more charge-up Predator blade lobbing off Marine's heads here. I'll skip talking about the boss fights across all three species as they're just annoying chores. The whole game was just a dull slog.  I guess if you grew up on Halo this game would be exciting, but I think I'll replay AvP Classic 2000 to remember what fun feels like.", "appid": "10680", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970502966", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571745600.0}
