{"text": "Hush is a neat little indie game that I immediately fell in love with the art style, but I sadly cannot really give any sort of proper review on this game because it is not that by any means. The game in its current state is a demo. No, I am not being overly harsh, but it does say â€œstart demoâ€ on the main screen, being a rather short 15 minutes. The opening animations do seem to imply some type of story, so without context we do not have anything to really follow. Movement is a little stiff but not difficult to navigate, and combat is not the best, as it is essentially moving back and forth and hitting once or twice before moving back again. That aside, it looks like the game would contain some small puzzles, I cannot say much besides the above, and it looks like there was a full game released based on the screenshots and videos, but looking at the announcements seems to imply that during the change of ownership something happened to revert back the game to an incomplete state. Verdict: 0/10 If you enjoyed this review please follow our curator", "appid": "379990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198199595411", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "75", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529582400.0}
