{"text": "So, this game yeah. It's not that great. The best way I can describe it to you is, it's alright. The games takes a lot of time to play by yourself, so you've got to make friends. Can't do that? Probably shouldn't play unless you've got more spare time than an asian networker.  The, even still, the gameplay is a bit wonky at best. Tunnels can't be filled in, the terrain is pretty hard to traverse, and materials can't be discerned until they are already in your inventory or if you know the texture. The amount of time it takes to learn how to play this game alone is pretty harsh, which is to be expected since you're literally building a kingdom right? But even then the game provides almost nooooo help at all. You have to look up where you MIGHT find materials, and this isn't even considering that you can get killed by players at any time. At the moment, I have the game and love, all it's flaws and all. But, I wouldn't recommend getting it yet, till it's at least out of early access.", "appid": "290080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198081258853", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1457352000.0}
