{"text": "This is quite honestly one of the laggiest and glitchiest games I have ever played. My PC is perfectly fine. I have a gtx 980, so my computer isn't the problem. Playing this game is extremely painful. You teleport around, objects get stuck in the walls, and simple tasks like cleaning your mop take immense concentration to not cause the bucket to teleport you across the room and kill you. I've died countless times just by walking into wet floor signs and random clipboards and bullet casings strewn across the floor. I mostly bought this game for its multiplayer, and trust me, I could write for days about how awful that experience was. The underlying gameplay for Viscera Cleanup Deatail isn't nesesarily boring, just almost impossible due to the buggy and uncontrollable physics.", "appid": "246900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198053549889", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1546084800.0}
