{"text": "There are very, very few story missions. Instead, most of the game are filler side missions, which you are probably already tired of doing when you completed SR4. Remember the well crafted missions back in SR3? Yeah there's none of that.  How about the soundtrack that made SR3 and SR4? Which song is this game's \"Holding Out for a Hero\" or \"The Touch\"? Well...there's not a single song in this game, all you hear is ambient noise and explosion most out of the time. As for the superpowers, Blast, Buff and Stomp are basically the same, Teleknesis got replaced with Summon. Super Sprint is exactly the same as before. The only thing really new to this game is that you can flap your wings to fly instead of gliding in SR4. I admit I really enjoy it. But at the same time, they took away Death From Above and Force Field for no reason. So don't be confused that you only got 6 powers now. In the end, all you've got is a sandbox that's less interesting that Steelport in SR3/4 and a game that lacks the production quality of SR3/4. I know that this game is an expansion standalone. You shouldn't except too much from it. But Far Cry 3: Blood Dragon was also standalone, look at what UBISOFT did with that game? The only reason I don't feel cheated is I've got this for $5.43 because of a price error. I can't recommend this game at $20.", "appid": "301910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090629272", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "39", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1421841600.0}
