{"text": "What utter and complete garbage. It's a pseudo-horror walking simulator with bad walking and bad scenery. You have the choice of using a lantern, which means that you can wander around without being able to see because it's pitch black or wander around without being able to see because the lantern is HUGE and RIGHT IN YOUR FREAKING FACE and puts off a METRIC CRAP-TON OF LIGHT to the point where literally everything around you is simply a wash of hazy white. So once you accept that you will be squinting and ruining your eyes throughout the entire ordeal, you realize that the \"plot\" consists of finding some notes and then wandering from one dimly-lit place to the next dimly-lit place that you can see ahead. You're supposed to meet \"Mr. Ben,\" who is, of course, nowhere to be seen. There is an occasional jump-scare in the form of some static image that suddenly takes over the screen, and then you move on. Don't bother exploring...you're never rewarded for it, and there's literally nothing interesting to see. SPOILER ALERT: You'll continue to wander for 10-20 minutes (depending upon whether you make the mistake of exploring like I did), and then come to the final bit where a guy from the KKK will jump out and stab you to death. The End. No, I'm not @#$!ing kidding. And then you see your coffin and Mr. Ben's coffin right there and three dudes in hoods are doing jaunty Fortnite-style dances near them. Seriously? The only way this ends is to be killed by a bunch of racists and then be taunted by them dancing around like they won the lottery? If this is someone's idea of original or even acceptable material, they should be locked in a portable toilet and kicked down a hill. This is a new low as far as I'm concerned. Everything about this game is bad, except the fairly-decent ambient sounds. The dev should be embarrassed for having written it, and I'm surprised that it hasn't been banned for content. TLDR: It's a low-rent horror/walking game with no options or point. Everything about it is bad, and it involves being killed by racists who celebrate your death. You should not only avoid it, but if you meet the jerk who coded it, you'd be within bounds to punch them in the face. 0/10 - there's a special place in hell for people who write games like this", "appid": "1010540", "steamid": "profiles/76561197975413392", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582200000.0}
