{"text": "This game was a massive letdown for me. I went into it thinking it would be a game about (apparent) isolation in the wilderness, and what I got was a game that featured constant radio chatter, with no flow whatsoever. The game is broken up into days, and the days usually feature tasks you need to complete before moving onto the next day. The game is very stop-start which impacted on the enjoyment of the game for me.  The game features a free roam mode which, although I haven't tried yet, I know I will enjoy much more than the story element of the game (You need to complete the story to unlock the free roam mode). The story is not very long at all, 3-4 hours maximum.  At full price it is a hard 'no recommendation'.  At Â£3.74 (75% off), it is personal preference if you still want to buy it or not.", "appid": "383870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198016420741", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529928000.0}
